theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_inter_subset_inter
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (A ∩ B : Set X))) ⊆
      closure (interior A) ∩ closure (interior B) := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, prove membership in `closure (interior A)`.
  have hxA : x ∈ closure (interior A) := by
    -- Establish an inclusion of sets:
    have h_subA :
        interior (closure (A ∩ B : Set X)) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      -- Step 1: `interior (closure (A ∩ B)) ⊆ interior (closure A)`.
      have h₁ :
          interior (closure (A ∩ B : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
        intro y hy
        have h_pair :=
          (Topology.interior_closure_inter_subset_inter
            (X := X) (A := A) (B := B)) hy
        exact h_pair.1
      -- Step 2: `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
      have h₂ :
          interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
        Topology.interior_closure_subset_closure_interior
          (X := X) (A := A)
      exact Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂
    -- Apply `closure_mono` to transport membership.
    have h_closureA :
        closure (interior (closure (A ∩ B : Set X))) ⊆
          closure (interior A) :=
      closure_mono h_subA
    exact h_closureA hx
  -- Next, prove membership in `closure (interior B)`.
  have hxB : x ∈ closure (interior B) := by
    -- Establish an inclusion of sets:
    have h_subB :
        interior (closure (A ∩ B : Set X)) ⊆ closure (interior B) := by
      -- Step 1: `interior (closure (A ∩ B)) ⊆ interior (closure B)`.
      have h₁ :
          interior (closure (A ∩ B : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure B) := by
        intro y hy
        have h_pair :=
          (Topology.interior_closure_inter_subset_inter
            (X := X) (A := A) (B := B)) hy
        exact h_pair.2
      -- Step 2: `interior (closure B) ⊆ closure (interior B)`.
      have h₂ :
          interior (closure B) ⊆ closure (interior B) :=
        Topology.interior_closure_subset_closure_interior
          (X := X) (A := B)
      exact Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂
    -- Apply `closure_mono` to transport membership.
    have h_closureB :
        closure (interior (closure (A ∩ B : Set X))) ⊆
          closure (interior B) :=
      closure_mono h_subB
    exact h_closureB hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB

theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_closure_of_isOpen_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h_open : IsOpen (closure (A : Set X))) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) = closure A := by
  -- `closure A` is always closed.
  have h_closed : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X)) := isClosed_closure
  -- Apply the existing lemma for sets that are both closed and open.
  simpa [closure_closure] using
    Topology.interior_closure_eq_self_of_isClosed_isOpen
      (X := X) (A := closure A) h_closed h_open
